**Website Logo**
===============

The website logo is a crucial element of a website's branding and identity. In this section, we will discuss the implementation of the website logo using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.

**HTML Structure**
-----------------

The HTML structure for the website logo is straightforward. We will use an `img` tag to display the logo image.
```html
<!-- index.html -->
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Website Logo</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <img src="img/logo.png" alt="Website Logo" id="logo">
    </header>
    <script src="script.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
```
**CSS Styling**
----------------

We will use CSS to style the website logo. We will add some basic styling to the `img` tag to make it look more appealing.
```css
/* styles.css */
#logo {
    width: 100px;
    height: 100px;
    margin: 20px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
}

#logo:hover {
    transform: scale(1.1);
    transition: transform 0.2s ease-in-out;
}
```
**JavaScript Functionality**
---------------------------

We will use JavaScript to add some interactivity to the website logo. We will make the logo rotate when the user hovers over it.
```javascript
// script.js
const logo = document.getElementById('logo');

logo.addEventListener('mouseover', () => {
    logo.style.transform = 'rotate(360deg)';
    logo.style.transition = 'transform 0.5s ease-in-out';
});

logo.addEventListener('mouseout', () => {
    logo.style.transform = 'rotate(0deg)';
    logo.style.transition = 'transform 0.5s ease-in-out';
});
```
**PHP Backend**
----------------

We will use PHP to handle the backend logic for the website logo. We will create a PHP script that will handle the logo upload and display.
```php
// logo.php
<?php
// Configuration
$logoPath = 'img/logo.png';

// Upload logo
if (isset($_FILES['logo'])) {
    $logoFile = $_FILES['logo'];
    $logoName = $logoFile['name'];
    $logoTmpName = $logoFile['tmp_name'];
    $logoSize = $logoFile['size'];
    $logoType = $logoFile['type'];

    // Validate logo
    if ($logoType == 'image/png' || $logoType == 'image/jpeg') {
        if ($logoSize < 1024 * 1024) {
            move_uploaded_file($logoTmpName, $logoPath);
            echo 'Logo uploaded successfully!';
        } else {
            echo 'Logo size exceeds 1MB!';
        }
    } else {
        echo 'Invalid logo type!';
    }
}

// Display logo
if (file_exists($logoPath)) {
    echo '<img src="' . $logoPath . '" alt="Website Logo">';
} else {
    echo 'No logo uploaded!';
}
?>
```
**MySQL Database**
------------------

We will use MySQL to store the website logo information. We will create a table to store the logo details.
```sql
-- logo.sql
CREATE TABLE logos (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY AUTO_INCREMENT,
    logo_name VARCHAR(255),
    logo_path VARCHAR(255),
    logo_size INT,
    logo_type VARCHAR(255)
);

INSERT INTO logos (logo_name, logo_path, logo_size, logo_type)
VALUES ('website_logo', 'img/logo.png', 1024, 'image/png');
```
**Core PHP Ecosystem**
----------------------

We will use the Core PHP ecosystem to handle the website logo functionality. We will create a PHP class to handle the logo upload and display.
```php
// Logo.php
class Logo {
    private $logoPath;
    private $logoName;
    private $logoSize;
    private $logoType;

    public function __construct($logoPath, $logoName, $logoSize, $logoType) {
        $this->logoPath = $logoPath;
        $this->logoName = $logoName;
        $this->logoSize = $logoSize;
        $this->logoType = $logoType;
    }

    public function uploadLogo() {
        // Upload logo logic
    }

    public function displayLogo() {
        // Display logo logic
    }
}
```
